{
  "texts": [
    "Briefly, 200 µL medium sample was mixed with 800 µL methanol containing internal standards (6 µL Splash Lipidomix).",
    "120 µL 0.2 M HCl, 400 µL chloroform, 400 µL chloroform, and 400 µL H 2 O were added to the mix consecutively and vortexed.",
    "The lower phase of the spun-down samples was collected with a 200 µL micro syringe (Hamilton, Reno, USA) and evaporated to dryness at 45 °C under nitrogen.",
    "Samples were stored at -80 °C.",
    "Water-soluble metabolites from organoid and culture medium samples were dissolved in 200 µl 5 mM ammonium acetate (in 75% acetonitrile (v/v)) before loading to LC/MS."
  ]
}